                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.60i11/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Young</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-13T16:00:00+01:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 14—1:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. Your September 11th, 1 p.m., will be promptly complied with. Consul Albrecht
                    now here leaving for Reval within a few days.</p>
                <p>Would our Government object to the sending of an Esthonian representative to the
                    United States to act unofficially as Esthonian agent, same status as Lettish
                    representative, Ozols, now at New York whom Latvia regards as consul, but who is
                    not of course recognized by us as such. Please reply by telegraph
                    immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
